# Error Resolution Logging

## Rule

When you encounter and fix an error during development, **append an entry to `ERROR_FIX_LOG.md`** using the template format:

```markdown
### [DATE] - Brief Description
**Error:** What went wrong
**Context:** What you were doing when it happened
**Root Cause:** Why it happened
**Fix:** How you resolved it
**Prevention:** How to avoid it in the future
```

## When to Log

- Build or compilation failures
- Runtime errors during ingestion, embedding, or retrieval
- API errors (rate limits, auth failures, timeouts)
- Database errors (schema mismatch, connection issues, query failures)
- Deployment errors (CORS, cold starts, missing env vars)
- Any error that took more than 5 minutes to diagnose

## When NOT to Log

- Typos caught immediately
- Linter warnings resolved inline
- Expected test failures during TDD

## Categories to Tag

Use these prefixes in the brief description:
- `[INGEST]` -- File discovery, preprocessing, chunking issues
- `[EMBED]` -- Embedding API errors, dimension mismatches
- `[DB]` -- pgvector/Supabase schema, connection, query issues
- `[RETRIEVE]` -- Search quality, ranking, context assembly issues
- `[LLM]` -- Claude API errors, prompt issues, hallucination
- `[DEPLOY]` -- Vercel, Railway, Supabase deployment issues
- `[UI]` -- Frontend rendering, API connection issues
